# Dialogs & Sheets

## UI choice (follow this matrix)

| Action | Component | Example |
|--------|-----------|---------|
| Create / Edit | **Sheet** (right side) | `branch-form-sheet.tsx` |
| Delete | **AlertDialog** | `ConfirmDeleteDialog`, `branch-delete-dialog.tsx` |
| Heavy workflow | **Dialog** (center) | upload, PDF merge, WhatsApp confirm |
| Filters | **FiltersSheet** | `components/filters-sheet.tsx` |

## Prefer

**Delete confirmation** — reuse `components/confirm-delete-dialog.tsx` or domain wrapper:

```tsx
<ConfirmDeleteDocumentDialog
    open={!!deleteDocId}
    onOpenChange={(open) => !open && setDeleteDocId(null)}
    onConfirm={() => router.delete(url, { onSuccess: () => setDeleteDocId(null) })}
/>
```

Reference: `features/organization/documents/shared/document-management-dialogs.tsx`

**Form sheet** — `Sheet` + `SheetHeader` + scrollable body + footer actions:

Reference: `features/organization/branches/components/branch-form-sheet.tsx`

**Multi-dialog state** — `useDialogState<'approve' | 'reject'>()` from `hooks/use-dialog-state.tsx`

**Lazy heavy modals** — `lazy(() => import('...'))` + `Suspense` (PDF merge):

Reference: `pages/organization/documents/employee.tsx`

## State pattern

```tsx
const [editDoc, setEditDoc] = useState<DocumentProfileItem | null>(null);
const [deleteDocId, setDeleteDocId] = useState<number | null>(null);
```

Open by setting entity; close in `onOpenChange` or `onSuccess`.

## Show page deletes

Pass `deleteRedirectUrl` to redirect after delete on detail pages:

Reference: `pages/organization/documents/show.tsx` → `DocumentManagementDialogs`

## Avoid

- `Dialog` for standard CRUD forms — use `Sheet`.
- Delete without confirmation dialog.
- Nesting dialogs unless an existing pattern does (rare).

## Domain dialog locations

- Shared delete: `components/confirm-delete-dialog.tsx`
- Documents: `features/organization/documents/shared/document-management-dialogs.tsx`
- Crew deployments: `features/organization/crew-deployments/deployment-form-dialog.tsx`
- Master data: `components/settings/master-data-form-sheet.tsx`
